HEADWORD: Desquamation
<hw>Des`qua*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>desquamation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The separation or
shedding of the cuticle or epidermis in the form of flakes or scales;
exfoliation, as of bones.</def></p>

